<subSubSection id="C32E54C8163BFFD4B59EE0516891CB3A" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8B0743163BFFD4B59EE0516A5FCEEC" blockId="45.[160,1156,886,1606]" box="[160,262,886,912]" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B59EE0516A5FCEEC" bold="true" box="[160,262,886,912]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B0743163BFFD4B59EE0BC6977C9B4" blockId="45.[160,1156,886,1606]" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">
<bibRefCitation id="EFA57AB2163BFFD4B59EE0BC6A67CECF" author="Bolton B" box="[160,318,923,947]" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" pagination="193 - 384" refId="ref17817" refString="Bolton B. 1980. The ant tribe Tetramoriini. The genus Tetramorium Mayr in the Ethiopian Zoogeographical region. Bull Br Museum (Nat Hist) Entomol. 40: 193 - 384." type="journal article" year="1980">
<collectingRegion id="49F0C9A1163BFFD4B59EE0BC6BB3CECF" box="[160,234,923,947]" country="United Kingdom" name="Bolton" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Bolton</collectingRegion>
(1980)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B4D3E0BC6841CECF" authorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[493,792,923,947]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transformans">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B4D3E0BC6841CECF" box="[493,792,923,947]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium transformans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B648E0BC6F24CECF" baseAuthorityName="Roger" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[886,1149,923,947]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caldarium">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B648E0BC6F24CECF" box="[886,1149,923,947]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium caldarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B42CE0996960CEAA" authorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[274,569,958,982]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transformans">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B42CE0996960CEAA" box="[274,569,958,982]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium transformans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be readily separated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B69FE0996B93CE84" baseAuthorityName="Roger" baseAuthorityYear="1857" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caldarium">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B69FE0996B93CE84" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium caldarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: cephalic dorsum with scattered longitudinal feeble rugulae, with ground-sculpture shining and weakly imbricate. Frontal carinae less-developed, ending back at the posterior levels of eyes. Whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B671E7016F0AC942" baseAuthorityName="Roger" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[847,1107,1062,1086]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caldarium">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B671E7016F0AC942" box="[847,1107,1062,1086]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium caldarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the cephalic dorsum feebly densely finely longitudinally rugulose, with ground-sculpture dull, finely, conspicuously punctulate or granulate. Frontal carinae well-developed running back beyond the posterior levels of eyes, feebly defined, and interrupted before reaching posterior margin of head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B0743163BFFD4B5FEE7F46891CB3A" blockId="45.[160,1156,886,1606]" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B5FEE7F46A87C997" authorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[192,478,1235,1259]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transformans">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B5FEE7F46A87C997" box="[192,478,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium transformans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as a strain under 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B696E7F46A46C872" authority="Forel, 1907" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B696E7F46FDAC997" box="[936,1155,1235,1259]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium pauper</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFA57AB2163BFFD4B59EE7D16A46C872" author="Forel A" box="[160,287,1270,1294]" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" pagination="1 - 42" refId="ref19084" refString="Forel A. 1907. Formicides du Musee National Hongrois. Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici. 5: 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="1907">Forel, 1907</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Comparing 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B484E7D16986C872" authorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[442,735,1270,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transformans">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B484E7D16986C872" box="[442,735,1270,1294]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium transformans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B614E7D16F55C872" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1907" box="[810,1036,1270,1294]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B614E7D16F55C872" box="[810,1036,1270,1294]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, both are similar in body size, sculpture and pilosity, but 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B7A8E63F68EDC84C" authorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[662,948,1304,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transformans">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B7A8E63F68EDC84C" box="[662,948,1304,1328]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium transformans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily diagnosed by the larger eyes, with seven ommatidia in the longest row (EI 26), whereas eyes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B59EE6796A26C80A" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1907" box="[160,383,1374,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B59EE6796A26C80A" box="[160,383,1374,1398]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are consistently smaller, with four ommatidia in the longest row (EI 15). In addition, the frontal carinae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B708E6A76848C8E4" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1907" box="[566,785,1408,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauper">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B708E6A76848C8E4" box="[566,785,1408,1432]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium pauper</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are shorter and just reach back to midline of eyes, whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B4F2E68469A8C8C7" authorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[460,753,1443,1467]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transformans">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B4F2E68469A8C8C7" box="[460,753,1443,1467]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium transformans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a longer and stronger frontal carinae running back to the posterior level of eyes. The eyes structure and size are important diagnostic characters in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B705E6CF699FCB7C" authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1855" box="[571,710,1512,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B705E6CF699FCB7C" box="[571,710,1512,1536]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Francisco Hita Garcia &amp; Barry 
<collectingRegion id="49F0C9A1163BFFD4B108E6CF6FD9CB7C" box="[1078,1152,1512,1536]" country="United Kingdom" name="Bolton" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Bolton</collectingRegion>
, personal communication 2016), Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B7AEE52C68EFCB5F" authorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityName="Santschi" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[656,950,1547,1571]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transformans">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B7AEE52C68EFCB5F" box="[656,950,1547,1571]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium transformans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is removed from synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC0163BFFD4B46EE5096914CB3A" baseAuthorityName="Roger" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[336,589,1582,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caldarium">
<emphasis id="B940DB51163BFFD4B46EE5096914CB3A" box="[336,589,1582,1606]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="361">Tetramorium caldarium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and recognized as a valid species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF4B57CB1638FFD7B59EE58A6825CB9D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184343" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5184343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184343/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="362" startId="46.[160,225,1709,1732]" targetBox="[244,1072,142,1678]" targetPageId="46">
