<subSubSection id="C32E54C81639FFD6B59EE3AA6961CD90" pageId="47" pageNumber="363" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8B07431639FFD6B59EE3AA6A2ECDDB" blockId="47.[160,1155,141,236]" box="[160,375,141,167]" pageId="47" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis id="B940DB511639FFD6B59EE3AA6A2ECDDB" bold="true" box="[160,375,141,167]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="363">Geographic range</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B07431639FFD6B59EE3956961CD90" blockId="47.[160,1155,141,236]" pageId="47" pageNumber="363">
This species is originally described from 
<collectingCountry id="F32347D31639FFD6B74AE39569E1CDB6" box="[628,696,178,202]" name="Kenya" pageId="47" pageNumber="363">Kenya</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA57AB21639FFD6B7F9E395683ECDB6" author="Santschi F" box="[711,871,178,202]" pageId="47" pageNumber="363" pagination="41 - 148" refId="ref20275" refString="Santschi F. 1914. Voyage de Ch. Alluaud et R. Jeannel en Afrique Orientale, 1911 - 1912. Resultats scientifiques. Insectes Hymenopteres. II. Formicidae. Paris: Libr. A. Schulz; p. 41 - 148." type="book chapter" year="1914">Santschi 1914</bibRefCitation>
) and is recorded for the first time from 
<collectingCountry id="F32347D31639FFD6B472E3F36AF8CD90" box="[332,417,212,236]" name="Yemen" pageId="47" pageNumber="363">Socotra</collectingCountry>
Archipelago.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32E54C81639FFD6B59EE23F68C9CCA3" pageId="47" pageNumber="363" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B8B07431639FFD6B59EE23F694CCC4E" blockId="47.[160,1156,280,479]" box="[160,533,280,306]" pageId="47" pageNumber="363">
<emphasis id="B940DB511639FFD6B59EE23F694CCC4E" bold="true" box="[160,533,280,306]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="363">Ecological and biological notes</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8B07431639FFD6B59EE21B68C9CCA3" blockId="47.[160,1156,280,479]" pageId="47" pageNumber="363">
This species was collected from dry leaf litter under a tree of 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01639FFD6B6A8E21B6FDACC28" authority="Thunb" authorityName="Thunb" box="[918,1155,316,340]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" genus="Ficus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="47" pageNumber="363" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cordata">
<emphasis id="B940DB511639FFD6B6A8E21B6F74CC28" box="[918,1069,316,340]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="363">Ficus cordata</emphasis>
Thunb
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01639FFD6B598E2786A40CC0B" box="[166,281,351,375]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="47" pageNumber="363" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Moraceae</taxonomicName>
). Several workers were foraging in dry soil under a date palm tree. A nest was found in moist leaf litter rich in decaying organic materials of animal faeces and next to a stream near date palm trees. A nest was found in galleries of a termite nest under a rock and coexisting with a nest of 
<taxonomicName id="4C347CC01639FFD6B7B1E2E068D2CCA3" authorityName="Forel" authorityYear="1894" box="[655,907,455,479]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Monomorium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="363" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exiguum">
<emphasis id="B940DB511639FFD6B7B1E2E068D2CCA3" box="[655,907,455,479]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="363">Monomorium exiguum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
